            <h1 class="title">Our National History</h1>
            <hr class="divider">
            <div class="content">
                <p>
                    <img src="~/images/pkt_chapter_locations.png" class="image" alt="Chapter Locations" style="width:100%; max-width:100%; height:auto">
                </p>
                <p>
                    Phi Kappa Theta, established on April 29, 1959, at Ohio State University, has a rich and storied national history deeply intertwined with the development of American higher education and the fraternity movement. From its inception, Phi Kappa Theta has been committed to fostering brotherhood, scholarship, and leadership among its members, guided by its core values of faith, tradition, and leadership. As one of the youngest national fraternities, Phi Kappa Theta has rapidly grown into a prominent presence on college campuses across the United States.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Throughout its history, Phi Kappa Theta has been at the forefront of innovation within the fraternity community, pioneering new programs and initiatives to support the personal and professional development of its members. From its early days as a local fraternity at Ohio State University to its expansion into a national organization with chapters spanning coast to coast, Phi Kappa Theta has remained dedicated to promoting academic excellence, philanthropy, and service to others.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Phi Kappa Theta's national history is marked by its commitment to philanthropy and community service. The fraternity's philanthropic efforts have ranged from supporting local charities and community organizations to partnering with national nonprofits to address pressing social issues. Through service projects, fundraisers, and volunteer work, Phi Kappa Theta chapters have made a positive impact on their communities, embodying the fraternity's motto of "Give, expecting nothing thereof."
                </p>
                <p>
                    In addition to its focus on service and philanthropy, Phi Kappa Theta has a proud tradition of fostering leadership and personal growth among its members. Through a variety of leadership development programs, workshops, and seminars, the fraternity empowers its members to become effective leaders in their communities and beyond. Phi Kappa Theta's commitment to leadership extends beyond the college years, providing ongoing support and resources to alumni as they pursue careers and make a difference in the world.
                </p>
                <p>
                    As Phi Kappa Theta continues to evolve and adapt to the changing needs of its members and society, its national history serves as a testament to the enduring values of brotherhood, service, and leadership that have guided the fraternity for over six decades. With a strong foundation built on the principles of faith, tradition, and leadership, Phi Kappa Theta looks forward to a future filled with continued growth, success, and impact.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
